        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1529952287" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3741174526040475607">4.5 stars<br/><br/>If you like Science Fiction, this book is for you. If you like romance, this book is for you. If you like political suspense, this book is for you. If you like action, this book is for you…I think you’re getting the idea now! This book is worthy of discussion on any academic level. I found Reason for Existence extremely deep. Botelho has a talent for provoking thought.<br/><br/>When I finished the book, I actually had to stop and think. Seriously, just sit and think; I’ve never had this happen be</span>
  <span id="freeText3741174526040475607" style="display:none">4.5 stars<br /><br />If you like Science Fiction, this book is for you. If you like romance, this book is for you. If you like political suspense, this book is for you. If you like action, this book is for you…I think you’re getting the idea now! This book is worthy of discussion on any academic level. I found Reason for Existence extremely deep. Botelho has a talent for provoking thought.<br /><br />When I finished the book, I actually had to stop and think. Seriously, just sit and think; I’ve never had this happen before. I can’t imagine any two people coming out of this book with the same feelings or thoughts.<br /><br />Reason for Existence is not a fast read, but it IS a smooth read. Overall, I loved the book so I rate it with a strong 4.5 stars....Beth<br /><br /><br /><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.boundlessbookreviews.com">http://www.boundlessbookreviews.com</a><br /><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.facebook.com/BBReviews">https://www.facebook.com/BBReviews</a></span>
